On July 25, 2009, the White House released a readout of a call between President Obama and UK Prime Minister Gordon Brown. They praised the performance of US and UK troops in Afghanistan and emphasized the need to increase civilian assistance to support military efforts. They also discussed their commitment to ensuring security for the upcoming Afghan elections and beyond, in order to facilitate progress in governance, rule of law, policing, and economic development. Both leaders agreed to continue coordinating closely and to hold future consultations on various important issues.